Let $f$: \emph{A} $\rightarrow$ \emph{B} be a function. If \emph{C} $\subseteq$ \emph{A}, define

\begin{align*}
f(C) = \{f(x) \mid x \in C\}
\end{align*}

Prove that if $f$ is injective, then

\begin{align*}
f(C \cap D) = f(C) \cap f(D) \quad\text{for all sets } C, D \subseteq A
\end{align*}
